article.headline: Saint Mary's (Cal) 59, Cal Poly 54
article.story: SAN LUIS OBISPO, Calif. -- Rob Jones had 18 points and 12 rebounds and Saint Mary's made four free throws in the final seconds to hold on for a 59-54 victory against Cal Poly-San Luis Obispo on Saturday night. Brad Waldow added 13 points and Matthew Dellavedova 10 for the Gaels (5-1), who won on Cal Poly's floor for the first time in five meetings. Jones had three blocks. Will Donohue's layup with 13 seconds remaining got Cal Poly within 55-54, but Jorden Page made both attempts from the line at the other end. The Mustangs (5-3) could not get off a shot as Donahue turned the ball over, and Dellavedova sank two free throws to clinch the win. David Hanson led Cal Poly with 15 points.
